import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
plt.style.use('ggplot')
%matplotlib inline  
from _settings import * 

df = pd.read_csv(d+'processing/annual_sales/all.csv')

# for i in df.columns:
# 	print i
#print df.head(10)

df = df[['sale_month']]
df['count'] = 1
df = df.groupby(['sale_month']).sum()#,as_index=False).sum()

#print df.head(12)

ax = df['count'].plot(kind='bar', title ="Count of Sales by Month (Years 2003-2014)",figsize=(15,10),legend=True, fontsize=12)
ax.set_xlabel("Month",fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel("Count",fontsize=12)
plt.show()

df = df.sort(['count'], ascending=0)

print 'Here are the number of sales by month sorted descending:'
print df.head(12)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv(d+'processing/annual_sales/all.csv')

#print df.head(10)

df = df[['sale_month','borough']]
df['count'] = 1
dfg = df.groupby(['sale_month','borough'],as_index=False).sum()#,as_index=False).sum()

for i in df.borough.unique():
	print i
	#print dfg.head(10)
	df = dfg[(dfg.borough == i)]
	df = df[['sale_month','count']]
	df = df.set_index('sale_month')

	#print df.head(12)

	ax = df['count'].plot(kind='bar', title ="Count of Sales by Month for borough "+str(i),figsize=(15,10),legend=True, fontsize=12)
	ax.set_xlabel("Month",fontsize=12)
	ax.set_ylabel("Count of Sales",fontsize=12)
	plt.ylim(0, 35000)
	plt.show()

	df = df.sort(['count'], ascending=0)

	print 'Here are the number of sales by month sorted descending:'
	print df.head(12)

In [16]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

df = pd.read_csv(d+'processing/annual_sales/all.csv')

#print df.head(10)

df = df[['sale_month','building_class_category']]
df['count'] = 1
dfg = df.groupby(['sale_month','building_class_category'],as_index=False).sum()#,as_index=False).sum()

for i in sorted(df.building_class_category.unique()):
	#print dfg.head(10)
	df = dfg[(dfg.building_class_category == i)]
	df = df[['sale_month','count']]
	df = df.set_index('sale_month')

	#print df.head(12)

	ax = df['count'].plot(kind='bar', title ="Count of Sales by Month for "+i,figsize=(15,10),legend=True, fontsize=12)
	ax.set_xlabel("Month",fontsize=12)
	ax.set_ylabel("Count",fontsize=12)
	plt.ylim(0, 20000)
	plt.show()

	df = df.sort(['count'], ascending=0)

	print 'Here are the number of sales by month sorted descending:'
	print df.head(12)
